         <OBJECT_CONTRACT>
            <TITLE>
               <P>Interpreter equipment, system and services for training labs</P>
            </TITLE>
            <REFERENCE_NUMBER>2018-152-000093</REFERENCE_NUMBER>
            <CPV_MAIN>
               <CPV_CODE CODE="32321200"/>
            </CPV_MAIN>
            <TYPE_CONTRACT CTYPE="SUPPLIES"/>
            <SHORT_DESCR>
               <P>Faculty of Arts at Aarhus University is establishing professional interpreting facilities with digital interpreting systems for our new professional Master’s programme “Master of Conference Interpretation” with up to 20 students.</P>
               <P>The facilities will consist of two training labs:</P>
               <P>— the system and the training situation should replicate the experience our students will have when working in the professional interpreting industry in EU, NATO, UNESCO etc.</P>
               <P>— the Contracting Authority requires a solution that consists of a professional conference and interpreting system, which is adapted for educational use and includes a fully integrated interpreter training system,</P>
               <P>— the Contracting Authority includes in the contract an option to buy extra equipment within the contract period. This is further described in clause 2.15,</P>
               <P>— it is optional for the Contracting Authority to use this option during the contract period,</P>
               <P>— the Service agreement in the Contract lasts for a 5-year period.</P>
            </SHORT_DESCR>
            <VAL_ESTIMATED_TOTAL CURRENCY="DKK">1600000.00</VAL_ESTIMATED_TOTAL>
            <NO_LOT_DIVISION/>
            <OBJECT_DESCR ITEM="1">
               <n2016:NUTS CODE="DK042"/>
               <SHORT_DESCR>
                  <P>The Contract includes delivery of an interpreting system, equipment for the training lab and a service agreement. furthermore, an option to buy extra equipment is included in the Contract.</P>
                  <P>Please note that the following items are not subject to this tender:</P>
                  <P>The university will supply:</P>
                  <P>— 20 student PC’s and screens,</P>
                  <P>— 2 teacher-PCs and screens,</P>
                  <P>— 2 Cisco video conference systems,</P>
                  <P>— loudspeakers, screens, and projectors in the two labs,</P>
                  <P>— Power and LAN-network up to an agreed point in the room,</P>
                  <P>— interpreter booths,</P>
                  <P>— Furniture (chairs and tables).</P>
               </SHORT_DESCR>
               <AC_PROCUREMENT_DOC/>
               <VAL_OBJECT CURRENCY="DKK">1600000.00</VAL_OBJECT>
               <DURATION TYPE="MONTH">60</DURATION>
               <NO_RENEWAL/>
               <NO_ACCEPTED_VARIANTS/>
               <OPTIONS/>
               <OPTIONS_DESCR>
                  <P>The option to buy extra equipment regards 1 (one) Teacher control centre, 5 (five) delegate units and 5 (five) interpreter units in compliance with the requirements stated in Appendix 1 Specification of Requirements. It is optional for the Contracting Authority to use this option in the contract period.</P>
               </OPTIONS_DESCR>
               <NO_EU_PROGR_RELATED/>
            </OBJECT_DESCR>
         </OBJECT_CONTRACT>
